As of the [[census]]<ref name="census2">{{cite web |title=U.S. Census website |url=https://www.census.gov |accessdate=May 19, 2011 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> of 2010, there were 607 people living in the CDP. There were 225 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 90.4% White, 0.3% Black or African American, 0.3% American Indian and Alaska Native, 0.2% Asian, 0.2% Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, 7.2% some other race, and 1.3% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 10.5% of the population.

